      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly linked to clinical performance and regulatory submission requirements. Required Gradation 2: QoIs justified as relevant to the COU decision.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield force are standard ASTM F1717 performance metrics used in 510(k) submissions for spinal fixation systems. Force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield behavior relevant to construct failure mode. All three QoIs directly support the regulatory decision. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
