    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA modeling framework for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct meets acceptance criteria for all three QoIs (E/uval < 1.96 for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement). Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The Test conditions factor achieved Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; however, the team determined that the ASTM F1717 standard test configuration is the primary regulatory basis and that the shortfall does not materially affect the submission decision. Overall credibility assessed as Medium and the simulation results are accepted for use in the regulatory submission.",
